---
// Featured Projects section — curated, narrative-driven
---

<section class="section" id="projects">
	<div class="container">
		<h2 class="section-title">$ ls ./featured-projects</h2>
		<div class="projects-grid">
			<!-- Project 1: DataOps Platform -->
			<div class="project-card">
				<div class="project-header">
					<h3 class="project-title">DataOps Platform @ Wētā FX</h3>
					<div class="project-tags">
						<span class="tag">Python</span>
						<span class="tag">Airflow</span>
						<span class="tag">ClickHouse</span>
						<span class="tag">Ansible</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p class="project-narrative">
					Production on-premises data platform powering BI and ML workflows across Wētā FX. Built
					and maintains 25+ ETL pipelines ingesting from disparate sources — solving the persistent
					problem of unreliable, undocumented data hand-offs between departments.
				</p>
				<p class="project-impact">
					<span class="impact-label">Impact:</span> Eliminated recurring pipeline failures; stakeholder
					teams now rely on it as production-critical infrastructure.
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Project 2: Airflow OSS Contributions -->
			<div class="project-card">
				<div class="project-header">
					<h3 class="project-title">Apache Airflow — OSS Contributions</h3>
					<div class="project-tags">
						<span class="tag">Python</span>
						<span class="tag">Open Source</span>
						<span class="tag">Apache Airflow</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p class="project-narrative">
					Contributor to Apache Airflow — the de facto standard for data pipeline orchestration used
					by thousands of organizations worldwide. Contributions focus on stability, usability, and
					operator improvements drawn from real production experience.
				</p>
				<p class="project-impact">
					<span class="impact-label">Links:</span>
					<a
						href="https://github.com/apache/airflow"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
						class="project-link">GitHub →</a
					>
					<span class="placeholder-note">[PR links — add when available]</span>
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Project 3: Data Quality Monitoring -->
			<div class="project-card">
				<div class="project-header">
					<h3 class="project-title">Data Quality & Observability System</h3>
					<div class="project-tags">
						<span class="tag">Great Expectations</span>
						<span class="tag">Python</span>
						<span class="tag">GitLab CI</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p class="project-narrative">
					Designed and built a platform-wide data quality framework from the ground up using Great
					Expectations — moving the team from reactive fire-fighting to proactive anomaly detection.
					Integrated into the CI/CD pipeline so quality checks run automatically on every deploy.
				</p>
				<p class="project-impact">
					<span class="impact-label">Impact:</span> Dramatically reduced data incidents; stakeholders
					gained confidence to act on data without manual verification.
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Project 4: MLOps Pipeline -->
			<div class="project-card">
				<div class="project-header">
					<h3 class="project-title">Kubernetes MLOps Platform</h3>
					<div class="project-tags">
						<span class="tag">Kubernetes</span>
						<span class="tag">Kubeflow</span>
						<span class="tag">AWS EKS</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p class="project-narrative">
					Co-designed and built a Kubernetes-based MLOps platform at Chorus NZ to close the gap
					between data science experimentation and production deployment. Enabled model training,
					versioning, and serving pipelines within a unified, reproducible infrastructure.
				</p>
				<p class="project-impact">
					<span class="impact-label">Impact:</span> First production ML infrastructure at the organisation
					— made model deployment a routine operation rather than a heroic effort.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.section {
		padding: 4rem 0;
	}

	.container {
		max-width: 1000px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 1.5rem;
	}

	.section-title {
		font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		color: #a6e3a1;
		font-weight: 500;
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
	}

	.projects-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(440px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5rem;
	}

	.project-card {
		background: rgba(30, 30, 46, 0.6);
		border: 1px solid rgba(137, 180, 250, 0.15);
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 1.75rem;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
		position: relative;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.project-card::before {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		right: 0;
		height: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(90deg, #a6e3a1, #89b4fa);
		opacity: 0;
		transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
	}

	.project-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(137, 180, 250, 0.35);
	}

	.project-card:hover::before {
		opacity: 1;
	}

	.project-header {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.project-title {
		font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: #cdd6f4;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}

	.project-tags {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.4rem;
	}

	.tag {
		background: rgba(137, 180, 250, 0.08);
		color: #89b4fa;
		padding: 0.2rem 0.55rem;
		border-radius: 4px;
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
		border: 1px solid rgba(137, 180, 250, 0.2);
	}

	.project-narrative {
		color: #bac2de;
		line-height: 1.7;
		font-size: 0.92rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.project-impact {
		color: #6c7086;
		font-size: 0.88rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.impact-label {
		color: #f9e2af;
		font-weight: 600;
		font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
	}

	.project-link {
		color: #89b4fa;
		text-decoration: none;
		margin-left: 0.5rem;
	}

	.project-link:hover {
		color: #a6e3a1;
	}

	.placeholder-note {
		color: #45475a;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		font-style: italic;
		margin-left: 0.5rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.projects-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.section-title {
			font-size: 1.2rem;
		}
	}
</style>
